column10:
Not recommended because:
- AI suck (especially the humans one);
- The game is basically like this: find weapon, use it until it is broken, repair it, repeat all steps. When you get your first gun in ACT 2 you think the game will be different but you are going to use melee weapons 90% of the time;
- The side mission are all basically the same;
- Zombies can see you from 10Km away and they will run like people during covid time to get toilet paper. (A stealth mechanic in this game would have been awesome)

But if you want to have fun I recommend to:
- Play arena mode once you have all guns (handgun, shotgun and rifle), 1/2 good melee weapons and throwables: you will fight against all the different type of zombies of the game and you are going to use all of the weapons in order to survive;
- Play coop with friends;
- Play the game without using fury and repairing melee weapons (this challenge will incentives you to avoid enemies, use all your tools, use all kind of weapons and so on)

There are lots of better zombie you should check out:
- No More Room In Hell;
- Left 4 Dead 2;
- Project Zomboid.
